-- Aeon Postpones Opening Ceremony for Tianjin Shopping Center, Nikkei Says
-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 2010-09-24T05:00:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/aeon-postpones-opening-ceremony-for-tianjin-shopping-center-nikkei-says.html
Aeon Co. will postpone the opening
ceremony of a shopping center in Tianjin, China, due to delays
in installing equipment and training employees, the Nikkei
newspaper reported, citing the Japanese retailer.   The company plans to hold the ceremony within a month of
the original Sept. 29 date, according to the report.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Go Onomitsu in Tokyo at 
 gonomitsu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
